Defendant Mark Alan Freiberg in court with Attorney Avery L Goodrich.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for plea/sentencing.  As to plea:  AS TO COUNT #1:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty.  Judgment of conviction entered.
  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

Court advised defendant if he is not a citizen of the United States of America, that upon a plea of guilty or no contest for this offense, he could be deported, excluded from admission to his country, or denied naturalization under federal law.  
Court advised that the defendant will have to provide a DNA sample, to the Wisconsin State Crime Laboratory for DNA testing and pay a DNA surcharge.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be SIX (6) years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for THREE (3) years with credit for 19 days time served.  Defendant shall serve THREE (3) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program 
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Random urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Pay fine in the amount of ZERO;
 - Interlock Device for THIRTY-SIX (36) months to commence upon eligibility to reinstate license;
 - Operating Privileges suspended for THIRTY-SIX (36) months to commence upon eligibility to reinstate license;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Correction from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would be then be paid while on Extended Supervision.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Assessment and Driver Safety Plan.
